message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Ireland in the past 100 years is the Good Friday Agreement of 1998. This agreement brought an end to decades of violent conflict between unionist and nationalist communities in Northern Ireland, known as "The Troubles." It established a power-sharing government and incorporated various political, economic, and social reforms. The Good Friday Agreement is considered a major milestone in the peace process and has significantly contributed to the relative stability and peace in Northern Ireland since its signing.
